            <p>Mohamad Chamber<lb/>
                29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Sivan 5609.<lb/>
                1849<lb/>
                Dear Sir&#47;<lb/></p>
                <p>I am directed by the Gentlemen of the<lb/> Mohamad to convey to you their best Thanks for the<lb/> excellent sermon you delivered at Synagogue on the<lb/> 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> day of Passover.<lb/></p>
                <p>It is gratifying to the Mohamad<lb/> to bear testimony to the general satisfaction&#44; which both<lb/> the subject of your discourse&#44; and the able manner in<lb/> which it was delivered afforded the congregation&#8212;and<lb/> they trust that the approval manifested will be an<lb/> incentive to future exertions on your part to promote<lb/> by pulpit instruction&#44; the spiritual welfare of our community.<lb/></p>
                <p>I am&#44; Dear Sir<lb/>
                Yours &#38;c<lb/>
                S. Almosnino<lb/>
                Secretary<lb/>
                To<lb/>
                Mr. S. Morais&#8212;<lb/></p>
            
        </body>
    </text>
